      • save

        public void save(VisitorMemento visitorMemento)
        Description copied from interface: MementoCaretaker
        Stores a copy of a VisitorMemento. It is the client's responsibility to remove the saved VisitorMemento once it is no longer needed either by calling MementoCaretaker.forget(Visitable) or MementoCaretaker.remove(VisitorMemento).
        Specified by:
        save in interface MementoCaretaker
        Parameters:
        visitorMemento - the VisitorMemento to copy and store. After saving, mutations to this VisitorMemento should not alter the saved copy.

      • stash

        public <T extends VisitorMemento> void stash(T visitorMemento,
                                             Consumer<T> visitorMementoConsumer)
        Description copied from interface: MementoCaretaker
        Invokes a Consumer with a restored VisitorMemento and then saves the VisitorMemento. This method offers a convenient way to aggregate and save data instead of writing: 
         mementoCaretaker.restore(visitorMemento);
 // add data to visitorMemento
 // ...
 mementoCaretaker.save(visitorMemento);
        Specified by:
        stash in interface MementoCaretaker
        Parameters:
        visitorMemento - the VisitorMemento to be restored
        visitorMementoConsumer - the consumer acting on the restored VisitorMemento
        See Also:
        MementoCaretaker.restore(VisitorMemento), MementoCaretaker.save(VisitorMemento)

      • restore

        public void restore(VisitorMemento visitorMemento)
        Description copied from interface: MementoCaretaker
        Mutates a VisitorMemento to match the state of a saved VisitorMemento. The VisitorMemento parameter is restored from a saved VisitorMemento having an ID equal to its ID as returned by VisitorMemento.getId(). The VisitorMemento parameter remains unchanged if no such saved VisitorMemento exists.
        Specified by:
        restore in interface MementoCaretaker
        Parameters:
        visitorMemento - the VisitorMemento to restore
